                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Decoration<p>Fine historiated and other borders and initials. Humanistic script
                        attributable to <persName role="scribe" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/162949">Bartolomeo Fonzio</persName>. Indian miniature made for Sir Elijah Impey,
            1775, inserted on fol. 5. (P&amp;A ii. 315, pl. XXIX)</p>
                        <list type="gloss">
                           <head>fol. 5v</head>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">miniature</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Inserted Indian miniature with a young man in long
                  tunic and headdress, holding a gold staff, with his hand over the shoulders of
                  a young woman in long dress, cloak and veil.</seg>
                           </item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="gloss">
                           <head>fol. 7r</head>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">initial F(rancesco)</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Gold 4-line initial with vine-stem decoration on a
                  multicoloured ground.</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">border, upper, left and lower
                  margin</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">The border is formed by double gold bars and vine-stem
                  decoration on a multicoloured ground, with an owl, peacock (?) and gold disks.
                  At the bottom of the page two winged putti support a laurel wreath with the
                  coat of arms of Francesco Sassetti.</seg>
                           </item>
                        </list>
                        <p>3- to 4-line gold initials and borders in left and upper margins,
            formed by sprays of flowers, leaves, fruit and gold disks, on fols. 14r, 138r,
            190r. Border on fol. 14r includes an elaborate urn.</p>
                     </decoNote>
